    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <head>Biographical History</head>
      <p>Will Barker (1908-?) was an American author from Troy, New York.  Following his military service, 
		he enrolled in the Veterans Authors Workshop which started him on a career as a full-time 
		writer.  In addition to several natural history books for children and numerous articles, he wrote for the U.S. 
		Fish and Wildlife Service (1949-1954) and edited books for the New York Times Book Review.  He 
		also lectured, appeared at children's book fairs, did the photography and illustrations for 
		his own books, and taught seminars at writing workshops.  He received awards from the National 
		Wildlife Federation for his work in conservation education.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
      <p>The 
        
        <emph render="bold">Will Barker Papers</emph> consist of corespondence, writings, published material and memorabilia.</p>
      <p>
        <emph render="bold">Correspondence</emph> has both business and personal letters dating from 1852 to 1970.</p>
      <p>
        <emph render="bold">Writings</emph> contains material for five nature books, several articles, and lectures for school and writing workshops.  Also included is some of Barker's editing work.</p>
      <p>
        <emph render="bold">Published material</emph> includes mainly books, magazines and newspapers.</p>
      <p>
        <emph render="bold">Memorabilia</emph> contains photographs, scrapbooks, personal papers, material on family history, and a small amount of Masonic papers.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
      <head>Arrangement of the Collection</head>
      <p>Correspondence is arranged chronologically.  All other series are arranged alphabetically.</p>
    </arrangement>
